        <actionDate>2020-08-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-09-21T18:21:11Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Criminal Judicial Administration Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill expands the authority of a judge to provide transportation and related expenses to a defendant to travel to a federal criminal court proceeding and also authorizes a magistrate judge to rule on post-judgment motions in certain criminal cases. (A magistrate judge assists a district court judge and exercises certain authority delegated by the district court judge to the magistrate judge, such as conducting trials in certain misdemeanor cases if the defendant consents.) </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
